description:
Is the Seventh-day Adventist Church God's remnant? Thirty years ago it was, but today its hardly recognizable as the remnant. Why?

Every pillar of Adventism has been attacked. Spiritualistic practices and worldliness have replaced the preaching of Christs imminent return. The trumpet sound of approaching conflict can be heard at our gates.  Will we follow the example of ancient Israel and be swept away? Or will we return to our work and prepare the way for Christs return? Will we be the remnant, people God can use, in these last days?

In this presentation, Walter Veith examines the typology of Proverbs 7. Discover lessons that apply to the remnant. 


Discover more: 
http://amazingdiscoveries.org
http://amazingdiscoveries.tv
